Operatives of the Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS) have arrested 10 persons for suspicion of armed robbery, kidnapping/cultism, gun running, and being in possession of suspected hard drug. The suspects who were arrested at various locations in Aba and Umuahia, the Abia state capital were paraded before newsmen at the police headquarters in the state capital. Speaking to newsmen, the Commissioner of Police (CP) in the state, Mr. Ene Okon, said the suspects have confessed to the crimes and will soon be arraigned in courts for prosecution. He said, “One of these was the robbery and shooting of one Basil Okechukwu ‘m’ of Obowo in Imo state on 16 January, 2020 around the General Post along Aba Road while on transit with money. The police boss said items recovered from the suspects include a charm known as “Do as I say,” one locally made pistol, stolen hand set, and wraps of weeds suspected to be Indian Hemp. “It would be recalled that after the death of the dreaded and notorious armed robber, Sampson Iheukwumere Nwokocha “Grave”, Umuahia residents enjoyed a peaceful movement and social moments. Reacting to the allegation, the suspect who was caught with the charm, after robbing his victim, Onyinechi Vincent of N150,000.00 along Bank Road, in the capital, blamed his act on Satan. 